ht|b|at|^-Suppose, for example, that the opener has:

{|ih|psk7ha9874dtcakj82|at|}
^-
@1
|cs|3|ht|m|at| @0@1^n@3|at|^-
{|ih|psq9842h53dk872c94|at|}
^-|
cs|2|ht|m|at| @1^n@2|at|^-
{|ih|psat43hktd6532cqt9|at|}
^-
@0@1
Opposite the first hand 2@H could easily fail. Opposite the second hand 6@C is a big favorite to come home. This uncertainty makes opener's choice of calls on the next round very difficult. The wide range of responder's 2@H preference is the reason for opener's dilemma.|
